Thus the bright lily of the vale,
Takes and yet does not forsake,
Reminding us of what prevails,
In life’s sweet, gentle wake.

So let each bloom remind our hearts,
To treasure each step we take,
For in the garden’s bounded arts,
We dance and make joy’s stake.

- William Wordsworth
